                        <h3 class="h3 col-4 pb-4 font-weight-bold" style="color: blue;">Project Explantion </h3>


                        <p>For this website, I wanted to learn Node so I thought it would be the perfect opportunity to learn it while I implement this project.
                        </p>
                        <p> It is an image/product repository with the following features:
                            <ul class=" ml-auto ">
                                <li class="h4"> Image repository</li>
                                <ul class=" ml-auto ">
                                    <li class="h6"> upload products</li>
                                    <li class="h6"> delete products</li>
                                    <li class="h6"> edit/modify products</li>
                                    <li class="h6"> public status</li>
                                    <li class="h6"> see products from other users + themselves in their home feed</li>
                                </ul>
                                <br>
                                <p> Users can upload products with images, name, quantity and price to their inventory. These images are stored in a mongodb database.
                                    <br>Users can see all ther products in their inventory while, only their public products are shown in the home feed to others
                                </p>
                                <li class="h4"> User Database and Session</li>
                                <ul class=" ml-auto ">
                                    <li class="h6"> Sign up/Sign in</li>
                                    <li class="h6"> Only user has access to delete or modify their own products</li>
                                    <li class="h6"> passwords are hashed</li>

                                </ul>
                                <br>
                                <p> I implemented a database via mongodb and mongoose to store user information. Additonally, users are authenticated using Passport.js and their passwords are hashed before stored in the database <br> this also provides users
                                    with access to modify only their own products
                                </p>

                                <li class="h4"> Search Feature </li>
                                Users or non-users can search for a product name using the search bar
                            </ul>
                        </p>
